parameters:
Are you okay with this? Being treated like you're not even
human by someone like that...!

Section Chief: What's with you since a while ago. You're the one
who doesn't understand.

Section Chief: It's annoying when someone who knows nothing
interferes. We just need to keep quiet and follow orders
without doing anything unnecessary.

Section Chief: Hey, hey, I tossed it at you with a swing... Can
you even catch something that heavy with your bare hands...?
Section Chief: You've probably never dug a hole before, have you?

Section Chief: There are others who can do the detailed work. The
reason comes later. For now, just keep digging through the
wall.

(There is a mission, but I shouldn't act recklessly without
understanding the situation I'm in. I'll observe for a while
and gather information.)
With this tool, I see. How far should I dig?

Section Chief: Thinking about that is a waste of time. Anyway,
you'll keep working until your arms can't lift anymore, and
even when they can't, you'll still be made to work.
Section Chief: Well, I can at least teach you the trick to it.

Section Chief: Don't try to go all out from the start. Proceed
with moderate effort, letting some power off.

Is that so, much obliged. Indeed, if I break my body from
the start, I won't last long.

Section Chief: It happens all the time. Idiots who get all fired
up just because they're new here.

Section Chief: If those kinds of guys become the standard for
quotas, it's us who suffer. That's why I'm driving the point
home.

Section Chief: I'm not worried about you. It's us I'm worried
about... Seriously, naive idiots like you are such a hassle.

What did you say! If I've been listening correctly, you've
been calling me naive and an idiot...!
Section Chief: Hmph, are you saying it's not true?

I might not differ, but still...! There's something called
manners in speaking!!
Section Chief: Channel that anger into the holes in the wall then.

Section Chief: It's only after they're gone that people realize
how precious those feelings were...
Section Chief: That's all for now! Come on, get moving!
